{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778976922599,"sessionID":"ses_1ccc5124fffelzMFVLcElI37gx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_cqztRUk7he80uo2RdsZLOIp6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Implemented the requested terreic acid label updates for `GO:0180067` and `GO:0180069`, while retaining `CHEBI:233617 ! terreate` in the logical definition as the pH 7.3 chemical form.\n+\n+Also corrected `created_by` on these two terms from `PomBase:vw` to `vw`, consistent with GO `created_by` metadata practice. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+This PR addresses geneontology/go-ontology issue #31114 by updating the existing terreic acid/terreate GO terms rather than minting new IDs.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Renamed `GO:0180067` from `terreate biosynthetic process` to `terreic acid biosynthetic process`.\n+- Swapped the previous `terreic acid biosynthetic process` synonym to `terreate biosynthetic process` as a RELATED synonym.\n+- Renamed `GO:0180069` from `positive regulation of terreate biosynthetic process` to `positive regulation of terreic acid biosynthetic process`.\n+- Added `positive regulation of terreate biosynthetic process` as a RELATED synonym for `GO:0180069`.\n+- Updated the `GO:0180069` definition to match the standard positive regulation wording: “Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of ...”.\n+- Updated the `positively_regulates` comment label on `GO:0180069` to match the new primary label of `GO:0180067`.\n+- Corrected `created_by` for both terms from `PomBase:vw` to `vw`.\n+\n+The logical definition for `GO:0180067` continues to use `CHEBI:233617 ! terreate`, following GO chemical-entity guidance to use the pH 7.3 form in logical definitions while allowing a biologist-friendly primary label.\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+- Pre-validation before edits: `make -C src/ontology travis_build` passed.\n+- Post-edit validation: `make -C src/ontology travis_build` passed.\n+\n+The validation run emitted existing RHEA filtering warnings for unavailable RHEA IDs, but all ROBOT/SPARQL checks passed with 0 violations.\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: Issue context and comments were reviewed; requested changes were clear.\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: Current ontology validated before changes.\n+- [x] RESEARCH: N/A; no new biological claim or reference was introduced. Existing PMID:25265334 was retained.\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: Existing relevant GO terms were inspected with `obo-grep.pl`.\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: Checked `biosynthetic_process.yaml` and `positive_regulation.yaml`; edits preserve the existing logical definitions and align the positive regulation definition text with the pattern.\n+- [x] CHEMICAL-ENTITY: Checked chemical-entity guidance; retained `CHEBI:233617 ! terreate` as the pH 7.3 logical definition target.\n+- [x] EDITS: Used `obo-checkout.pl` and `obo-checkin.pl`; did not edit `go-edit.obo` directly.\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: No relationship semantics changed; logical definition remains `biosynthetic process` and `has_primary_output CHEBI:233617`, and regulation remains `positively_regulates GO:0180067`.\n+- [x] METADATA: Corrected `created_by` from `PomBase:vw` to `vw`; did not alter creation dates or term tracker links.\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make -C src/ontology travis_build` passed after edits.\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: No new references introduced; existing PMID retained.\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: Committed only `src/ontology/go-edit.obo`.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w